  "weixin_html": "<section style='background:#f4f8fc;'><img src='https://mmbiz.qpic.cn/mmbiz_gif/3hAJnwuyZuicicZkgJBUCCaricdibomDBrTzXgUR7FJnf11qGIo8nmKt6RxibXrb5s4RFb9UZ9UOHQy7fqQyI377Licw/0?wx_fmt=gif' style='width:100%;display:block;'><section style='padding:24px 16px 8px 16px;background:#ffffff;font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Helvetica Neue,PingFang SC,Hiragino Sans GB,Microsoft YaHei,sans-serif;'><section style='padding:18px 14px;border-radius:14px;background:linear-gradient(140deg,#f7fbff 0%,#eef5ff 100%);margin-bottom:22px;'><p style='margin:0 0 8px 0;font-size:13px;color:#61758a;line-height:1.7;'>NASA Daily · 2026-03-20</p><h1 style='margin:0;font-size:24px;line-height:1.38;color:#10243e;'>NASA 今日速递：3 条太空前沿动态一次看懂</h1><p style='margin:12px 0 0 0;font-size:15px;line-height:1.9;color:#364a60;'>今天的 NASA 动态集中在载人航天、深空任务和前沿技术验证。为了提高微信分发和完读率，我们按“强标题+关键信息卡片+互动提问”的结构整理了重点。</p></section><section style='margin:0 0 18px 0;padding:16px;border:1px solid #e8eef5;border-radius:14px;background:#ffffff;box-shadow:0 6px 16px rgba(20,35,54,0.06);'><h3 style='margin:0 0 8px 0;font-size:19px;line-height:1.45;color:#1b2c45;'>No.1 Artemis II Moon Rocket Heads Back to Launch Pad</h3><p style='margin:0 0 12px 0;font-size:13px;color:#64748b;line-height:1.7;'>NASA · March 20, 2026 12:26AM</p><img src='https://raw.githubusercontent.com/duguBoss/daily-nasa-hub/main/assets/generated/2026-03-20/20aa99c1b572-artemis-ii-moon-rocket-heads-back-to-lau.jpg' style='width:100%;display:block;border-radius:12px;margin:0 0 12px 0;object-fit:cover;'><p style='margin:0 0 10px 0;font-size:15px;line-height:1.92;color:#334155;'><strong>看点速读：</strong>NASA’s Artemis II SLS (Space Launch System) rocket and Orion spacecraft slated to send four astronauts around the Moon began rolling to Launch Pad 39B at 12:20 a.m. EDT on Friday, March 20. Rollout operations at the agen</p><p style='margin:0;font-size:14px;line-height:1.8;'><a href='https://www.nasa.gov/blogs/missions/2026/03/20/artemis-ii-moon-rocket-heads-back-to-launch-pad' style='color:#1565c0;text-decoration:none;'>查看 NASA 原文 ></a></p></section><section style='margin:0 0 18px 0;padding:16px;border:1px solid #e8eef5;border-radius:14px;background:#ffffff;box-shadow:0 6px 16px rgba(20,35,54,0.06);'><h3 style='margin:0 0 8px 0;font-size:19px;line-height:1.45;color:#1b2c45;'>No.2 Restless Kīlauea Launches Lava and Ash</h3><p style='margin:0 0 12px 0;font-size:13px;color:#64748b;line-height:1.7;'>NASA Science · 2026-03-20T00:01:00-04:00</p><img src='https://raw.githubusercontent.com/duguBoss/daily-nasa-hub/main/assets/generated/2026-03-20/1a8a970e390c-restless-k-lauea-launches-lava-and-ash-e.jpeg' style='width:100%;display:block;border-radius:12px;margin:0 0 12px 0;object-fit:cover;'><p style='margin:0 0 10px 0;font-size:15px;line-height:1.92;color:#334155;'><strong>看点速读：</strong>Episode 43 of the Hawaiian volcano’s current eruption was marked by high lava fountains and widespread ash dispersal. Kīlauea has entered its second year of episodic activity after reawakening in December 2024. Since the</p><p style='margin:0;font-size:14px;line-height:1.8;'><a href='https://science.nasa.gov/earth/earth-observatory/restless-kilauea-launches-lava-and-ash' style='color:#1565c0;text-decoration:none;'>查看 NASA 原文 ></a></p></section><section style='margin:0 0 18px 0;padding:16px;border:1px solid #e8eef5;border-radius:14px;background:#ffffff;box-shadow:0 6px 16px rgba(20,35,54,0.06);'><h3 style='margin:0 0 8px 0;font-size:19px;line-height:1.45;color:#1b2c45;'>No.3 Crew Enjoys Light-Duty Day, Debriefs Spacewalk</h3><p style='margin:0 0 12px 0;font-size:13px;color:#64748b;line-height:1.7;'>ISS Blog · March 19, 2026 12:04PM</p><img src='https://raw.githubusercontent.com/duguBoss/daily-nasa-hub/main/assets/generated/2026-03-20/e0090af911e2-crew-enjoys-light-duty-day-debriefs-spac.jpg' style='width:100%;display:block;border-radius:12px;margin:0 0 12px 0;object-fit:cover;'><p style='margin:0 0 10px 0;font-size:15px;line-height:1.92;color:#334155;'><strong>看点速读：</strong>Four International Space Station residents had a light-duty day Thursday as they enjoyed some time off and worked on close out procedures following the conclusion of yesterday’s spacewalk. The three other Expedition 74 c</p><p style='margin:0;font-size:14px;line-height:1.8;'><a href='https://www.nasa.gov/blogs/spacestation/2026/03/19/crew-enjoys-light-duty-day-debriefs-spacewalk' style='color:#1565c0;text-decoration:none;'>查看 NASA 原文 ></a></p></section><section style='margin:4px 0 20px 0;padding:16px;border-radius:12px;background:#fffaf0;border:1px solid #ffe4b8;'><p style='margin:0;font-size:15px;color:#5f4b2f;line-height:1.9;'><strong>互动话题：</strong>今天这几条 NASA 动态里，你最想追踪哪一个任务后续？</p><p style='margin:8px 0 0 0;font-size:14px;color:#7b6543;line-height:1.9;'>如果这篇合辑有帮助，欢迎点在看并转发给同样关注太空探索的朋友。</p></section></section><img src='https://mmbiz.qpic.cn/mmbiz_gif/3hAJnwuyZuicicZkgJBUCCaricdibomDBrTzk57DCmhVC16o9ILH0Tn1YPEiarfLRRQSVFN2mJdeYibGnBPialPIzvojw/0?wx_fmt=gif' style='width:100%;display:block;'></section>",
